cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with stereo reconstruction from rectified images using deep learning. The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Conditional Random Fields (CRFs) also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of regularization techniques and inter-pixel interactions suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of hand-engineered post-processing steps suggests that it could belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
